						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#173;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#163;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#135;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#163;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#157;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#131;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136; (Candypot) is a shedding game from japan. Players have four lollipops and dispose of them by either giving them to the boy in the centre, or to other players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has four tokens, and choose one in secret, then show them to each other. The tokens allow them to do an action, but only if they are the only one doing that action. They can pass a lolly to another player, or they can eat the lolly by giving it to the boy in the middle of the table. So if two players both try to pass a lolly to a third player, they deny each other and keep their lollies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A third action is to block being passed a lollipop, and the final action is to retrieve your tokens. These two actions are not blocked by other players choosing the same action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when one player wins by emptying their hand of all lollipops.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is puplished in a small jam jar.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
